    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of an African ethnic group inhabiting the dry grassland country of northern Namibia and southern Angola. They are usually called Ovambo in Namibia and Ambo in Angola and speak Kwanyama, a Bantu language.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
